# Bauhaus/Experimental Jetset/Swiss-German Design System

## Design Influences
1. **Bauhaus** - Geometric, functional, minimal decoration, strong structure
2. **Experimental Jetset** - Modernist typography, grid-based layouts, precise spacing
3. **Swiss/German Package Design** - Helvetica/Akzidenz Grotesk, strong grids, functional color, information density

## Core Principles

| Principle | Implementation |
|-----------|----------------|
| Strong Grid | Visible, structural grid system with tight alignment |
| Sans-Serif Typography | All text uses sans-serif fonts (Helvetica Neue) |
| Density | Maximum information per viewport without losing readability |
| Geometric Precision | Square corners, aligned elements, no decoration |
| Functional Color | Monochromatic palette with minimal, functional accents |
| Minimum Text Size | All text must be at least 10px |

## Typography

```scss
// Font stacks
--font-primary: 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
--font-mono: 'SF Mono', Consolas, 'Liberation Mono', monospace;

// Base
--font-size-base: 14px;
--line-height-base: 1.4;

// Type Scale (minimum 10px, ratio 1.25)
--text-xs: 0.714rem;    /* 10px - meta, timestamps */
--text-sm: 0.75rem;     /* 12px - captions, secondary */
--text-base: 0.875rem;  /* 14px - body text */
--text-md: 1.094rem;    /* ~15px - card titles */
--text-lg: 1.367rem;    /* ~19px - section headers */
--text-xl: 1.709rem;    /* ~24px - page titles */
--text-2xl: 2.136rem;   /* ~30px - hero text */
--text-3xl: 2.67rem;    /* ~37px - display */
```

### Typography Rules
- **ALL CAPS**: Navigation, status labels, section headers
- **Sentence case**: Body text, descriptions
- **Tabular numerals**: All notation (i5, s23, 2609.5.56)
- **Letter-spacing**: -0.02em for headings, +0.02em for all-caps
- **No italics** except `<cite>` elements
- **Weights**: 400 body, 500 headings, 700 emphasis
- **All headings use sans-serif** (no serif fonts)

